1467
01:50:08,196 --> 01:50:10,255
even if that means coming to your house every night

1468
01:50:10,365 --> 01:50:12,060
until you finish the work.

1469
01:50:12,166 --> 01:50:13,963
I see who you are.

1470
01:50:14,503 --> 01:50:16,630
Do you understand me?

1471
01:50:17,640 --> 01:50:19,608
I can see you.

1472
01:50:21,477 --> 01:50:23,411
And you are not failing.

1473
01:50:26,849 --> 01:50:31,786
So, take a minute. Pull yourself together and come inside.

1474
01:50:32,321 --> 01:50:34,346
I want a new evaluation.

1475
01:50:39,561 --> 01:50:42,359
An F. What, are you tripping?

1476
01:50:48,037 --> 01:50:51,495
I want you all to know that Dr. Cohn and I tried very hard.

1477
01:50:54,277 --> 01:50:57,144
But it's been decided we can't continue with each other junior year.

1478
01:50:57,280 --> 01:50:58,372
-What? -What?

1479
01:51:00,016 --> 01:51:01,916
You... Wait.

1480
01:51:02,652 --> 01:51:04,620
Wait. Guys. Everyone.

1481
01:51:06,022 --> 01:51:08,490
No! That don't fly, Ma!

1482
01:51:10,060 --> 01:51:13,723
Look, first of all, I'm not anyone's mother in here, okay?

1483
01:51:13,830 --> 01:51:16,025
No, it doesn't mean mother.

1484
01:51:16,733 --> 01:51:19,065
It's a sign of respect for you.

1485
01:51:33,284 --> 01:51:34,683
Listen to me.

1486
01:51:34,919 --> 01:51:36,216
All of you.

1487
01:51:36,987 --> 01:51:41,617
Don't use me as another excuse for why you can't make it.

1488
01:51:43,527 --> 01:51:46,826
You made it to your junior year.

1489
01:51:47,631 --> 01:51:50,429
Think about how you did that.

1490
01:51:51,802 --> 01:51:55,465
Everyone in this room has a chance to graduate.

1491
01:51:56,507 --> 01:51:59,067
For some, you'll be the first in your family.

1492
01:51:59,176 --> 01:52:01,940
The first with a choice to go to college.

1493
01:52:02,948 --> 01:52:05,746
Some may move faster than others.

1494
01:52:07,352 --> 01:52:09,650
But you'll each have the chance.

1495
01:52:10,722 --> 01:52:13,691
And you did that. Not me.

1496
01:52:20,766 --> 01:52:24,429
Now, I have one

1497
01:52:26,471 --> 01:52:28,063
final project in mind.

1498
01:52:28,173 --> 01:52:30,368
-Ms. G. -Yeah?

1499
01:52:32,210 --> 01:52:37,170
Ms. G wanted us to put our diaries together in a book, just like Anne Frank.

1500
01:52:37,917 --> 01:52:39,942
She got this businessman, John Tu,

1501
01:52:40,086 --> 01:52:42,919
to donate 35 computers so we could work.

1502
01:52:47,994 --> 01:52:51,395
She told us we have something to say to people.

1503
01:52:51,564 --> 01:52:51,664
We weren't just kids in a class anymore.

1504
01:52:51,664 --> 01:52:53,962
We weren't just kids in a class anymore.

1505
01:52:54,066 --> 01:52:57,763
We were writers with our own voices, our own stories.

1506
01:52:57,870 --> 01:52:59,929
And even if nobody else read it,

1507
01:53:00,039 --> 01:53:03,634
the book would be something to leave behind that said we were here,

1508
01:53:04,243 --> 01:53:07,337
this is what happened, we mattered.

1509
01:53:07,814 --> 01:53:12,080
Even if it was just to each other. And we won't forget.

1510
01:53:13,787 --> 01:53:16,153
Ms. G didn't promise it would get published or anything,

1511
01:53:16,256 --> 01:53:19,123
but we could get it out there ourselves.

1512
01:53:19,860 --> 01:53:22,090
She asked us to come up with a title,

1513
01:53:22,629 --> 01:53:24,597
something to call ourselves.

1514
01:53:42,382 --> 01:53:44,247
I just received a call from Karin Polacheck

1515
01:53:44,384 --> 01:53:45,476
at the Board of Education.

1516
01:53:45,619 --> 01:53:47,610
There's to be a meeting with Dr. Cohn about your classes.

1517
01:53:47,755 --> 01:53:51,191
-Do you know anything about this? -No.

1518
01:53:59,000 --> 01:54:04,461
These students, this class, they've become a family.

1519
01:54:05,373 --> 01:54:06,965
To who? To you?

1520
01:54:07,642 --> 01:54:09,269
To each other.

1521
01:54:10,078 --> 01:54:13,411
Room 203 is a kind of a home for them.

1522
01:54:13,948 --> 01:54:17,281
Their trust is all wrapped up in us being together as a group.

1523
01:54:17,719 --> 01:54:18,845
Once they're out of her class,

1524
01:54:18,987 --> 01:54:21,421
believe me they'll slip back into their old habits.

1525
01:54:21,522 --> 01:54:25,481
Their reading scores, their writing has markedly improved, Ms. Campbell.

1526
01:54:25,628 --> 01:54:29,120
On paper. But what has she accomplished in reality?

1527
01:54:29,231 --> 01:54:30,858
What about new students that come in next year?

1528
01:54:30,966 --> 01:54:32,957
Can she repeat this process every year?

1529
01:54:33,068 --> 01:54:34,467
Her methods are impractical,

1530
01:54:34,570 --> 01:54:37,198
impossible to implement with regularity.

1531
01:54:37,306 --> 01:54:39,797
What if every teacher performed in this way?

1532
01:54:40,409 --> 01:54:41,637
We have millions of children

1533
01:54:41,744 --> 01:54:43,473
to get through the education system in this country,

1534
01:54:43,579 --> 01:54:45,410
and we need a means of accomplishing that

1535
01:54:45,514 --> 01:54:48,415
which allows as many students to benefit as possible,

1536
01:54:48,517 --> 01:54:50,451
not just special cases.

1537
01:54:51,954 --> 01:54:55,412
And you honestly think you can create this family in every classroom,

1538
01:54:55,557 --> 01:54:58,526
for every grade, for every student you teach?

1539
01:55:03,099 --> 01:55:04,566
I don't know.

1540
01:55:10,774 --> 01:55:12,105
Thank you.

1541
01:55:32,495 --> 01:55:35,396
Hey, there go Ms. G. Hey, there go Ms. G!

1542
01:55:44,308 --> 01:55:45,707
What happened?

1543
01:55:46,510 --> 01:55:50,310
So? Are we gonna be together for junior year?

1544
01:55:56,153 --> 01:55:57,450
No.

1545
01:55:58,389 --> 01:56:00,254
-What? -What?

1546
01:56:04,862 --> 01:56:08,229
We're gonna be together junior and senior year.

1547
01:56:09,667 --> 01:56:10,725
Yes!
